Based on other reviews, I added seared scallops and garlic to this recipe. First, I heated about 2 tablespoons of sweet butter with 1 tablespoon olive oil and sauteed four cloves of minced garlic in that. Increased the heat, seared 1/2 pound scallops, removed them to a plate, and used the garlic and butter remaining in the pan as the base for the sauce. Added the fresh, cooked pasta directly from it's pot without draining--just lifted it out and into the pan the scallops were cooked in, figuring it would hold on to about as much water as the recipe calls for. Also added about 1 tablespoon dried parsley, and omitted the salt. Increased the cheese to 1 cup. Very good, especially with freshly-made pasta (3 1/2c flour to 4 eggs).

